HEADWORD: Sinalbin
<hw>Sin*al"bin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From L.
<ets>Sin</ets>apis + <ets>alba</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
glucoside found in the seeds of white mustard (<spn>Brassica alba</spn>,
formerly <spn>Sinapis alba</spn>), and extracted as a white crystalline
substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

